H0.text: A large glacier forming on a mountain is the process that causes the fastest changes to the surface of Earth.

H1.text: Strong winds wearing away a rock cliff cause the fastest changes to the surface of Earth.

H2.text: A major earthquake happening in a mountain range is the process that causes the fastest changes to the surface of Earth.

H3.text: Many waves on a lake moving pebbles onto a beach cause the fastest changes to the surface of Earth.
